==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Zorilla
<hw>Zo*ril"la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.
<ets>zorilla</ets>, <ets>zorillo</ets>, dim. of <ets>zorra</ets>,
<ets>zorro</ets>, a fox: cf. F. <ets>zorille</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Either one of two species of small African
carnivores of the genus <gen>Ictonyx</gen> allied to the weasels and
skunks.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>zoril</asp>, and
<asp>zorille</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The best-known species (<spn>Ictonyx zorilla</spn>) has
black shiny fur with white bands and spots. It has anal glands which
produce a very offensive secretion, similar to that of the skunk. It
feeds upon birds and their eggs and upon small mammals, and is often
very destructive to poultry. It is sometimes tamed by the natives, and
kept to destroy rats and mice. Called also <altname>mariput</altname>,
<altname>Cape polecat</altname>, and <altname>African polecat</altname>.
The name is sometimes erroneously applied to the American
skunk.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Zoroaster</ent>⟦br⟧
